  "response": "The Master of Engineering (M.Eng) in Civil Engineering at the University of Alberta is typically a **course-based program** designed to be completed in **one to two years** of full-time study. The exact duration can vary depending on the student's pace, whether they are studying full-time or part-time, and the specific requirements of their program.\n\nFor full-time students, completing the program within **one year (12 months)** is common, but some students may take up to two years, especially if they are balancing other commitments or extending their studies.\n\nIt's always a good idea to check the latest program details on the University of Alberta's official website or contact the Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering for specific information about course requirements and duration.",
